properties.Title: Freezing Rain Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: Freezing rain will continue through the night at Arviat. This freezing rain will end or turn to snow Sunday morning. Freezing rain is likely occurring at Whale Cove tonight. There is a risk of freezing rain at Rankin Inlet as well tonight. ### Freezing rain warnings are issued when rain falling in sub-zero temperatures creates ice build-up and icy surfaces. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.

properties.Title: Snowfall Warning In Effect
properties.Summary:
Description: A low pressure system moving through Hudson Bay will bring 10 to 15 cm of snow to Coral Harbour. Snow will begin this morning in Coral Harbour and 10 cm of snow is expected during the day. Snow will likely be heavy at times and may result in reduced visibilities. Snowfall will taper off Sunday night and a few additional centimeters of snow are expected by Monday morning. ### Snowfall warnings are issued when significant snowfall is expected. Please continue to monitor alerts and forecasts issued by Environment Canada. To report severe weather, send an email to NUstorm@canada.ca or tweet reports using #NUStorm.
